Human Language: english
Teachpack filenames: ()
Computer Language: (("Professional Languages" "PLT" "Pretty Big (includes MrEd and Advanced)") #6(#t write mixed-fraction-e #f #t debug))
>Description:
Under Pretty Big (and PLAI - Pretty Big), "Check Syntax"
erroneously colors "false" red.

(Strangely, it correctly gets "true" blue.)
>How-To-Repeat:
Open file, switch to Pretty Big, type false,
hit Check Syntax.
>Fix:
The bug: to test if a value was bound in a namespace, the code used namespace-variable-value's result directly. When the variable was bound to #f, it was as if the test failed! Ack. The fix: use the thunk argument to namespace-variable-value properly with an escaping continuation.
>Release-Note:
there was no contract violation. just bad behavior.
